article.headline: Bradley 63, Indiana St. 52
article.story: TERRE HAUTE, Ind. -- Dodie Dunson scored 15 points to help Bradley defeat Indiana State 63-52 on Tuesday night. Theron Wilson scored 12 points and Sam Maniscalco added 11 for the Braves (11-6, 5-1 Missouri Valley). Rashad Reed scored 12 points, Jay Tunnell scored 11 and Aaron Carter and Jordan Printy each added 10 for the Sycamores (4-13, 2-4). Indiana State played without leading scorer Harry Marshall. Media reports say the guard hurt his hamstring Saturday against Illinois State and is day-to-day. Bradley led 28-22 at halftime, and led 48-46 before going on a 14-3 run to take a 62-49 lead with 1:11 to play. The Braves forced 15 turnovers and held the Sycamores to 34 percent shooting.
